<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Iddings</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-25"><hi rend="italic">August 25,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Iddings reports that the Italian Government has not replied to
                                the indirect communications of cables it has received from Earl Li
                                Hung Chang, dated August 19 and 21. His authority to negotiate not
                                being yet defined, they consider his suggestions premature. They
                                think the basis of negotiations should first be settled between the
                                powers.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>